@WaltonBob @EnvAgencyYNE Strange, I was only following the course of this cut on an @OrdnanceSurvey map yesterday and wondered what it was for.

The Sea Cut (Scalby Beck) is a man-made canalised beck to divert the River Derwent to the sea at Scalby Mills after it flooded in 1799. Opened in 1804, the Cut has ten weirs that control the energy of floodwaters; like today, under an amber flood alert.
